Add one of the following '????.modeset=0' parameter at the end of the long grub command line as is (type 1 space before).
Use the parameter related to the brand or chipset of your video card . pe.:
use nouveau  or nvidia for nvidia based cards (proprietary driver, just nv in some linux distributions,
nouveau driver is the default in Mint) ), use radeon for amd/ati cards, i915 for intel based motherboards, ,,,  These are the most common examples.

   nvidia.modeset=0  NVIDIA
   nouveau.modeset=0 NVIDIA
   radeon.modeset=0
   i915.modeset=0 
